And then you can actually test
that hypothesis and

00:27:56.870 --> 00:27:58.280
say, well, if I had more
content.

00:27:58.280 --> 00:27:59.730
Do I look at myself in the
mirror more often?

00:27:59.730 --> 00:28:00.360
Turns out you did.

00:28:00.360 --> 00:28:01.490
If you had more endorsements,

00:28:01.490 --> 00:28:02.750
did you look at yourself in
the mirror more often?

00:28:02.750 --> 00:28:03.650
Turns out you did.

00:28:03.650 --> 00:28:04.900
So, we actually figured out
like

00:28:04.900 --> 00:28:08.150
what was actually underneath
utilitarian product that

00:28:08.150 --> 00:28:09.130
the product team thought they
were

00:28:09.130 --> 00:28:11.210
building was actually a lot of
emotional vanity.

00:28:11.210 --> 00:28:14.260
They didn&#39;t exactly translate
it to the best possible

00:28:14.260 --> 00:28:15.590
feature, like the PayPal
example,

00:28:15.590 --> 00:28:17.100
which you couldn&#39;t easily put
a button that,

00:28:17.100 --> 00:28:19.333
said be more vain today, you
