00:33:21.721 --> 00:33:26.331
&gt;&gt; Instead of what&#39;s the how
many details

00:33:27.331 --> 00:33:28.987
&gt;&gt; You&#39;d be amazed.

00:33:28.987 --> 00:33:31.126
&gt;&gt; Well, yeah, so the question
was besides food what

00:33:31.126 --> 00:33:33.860
other kind of details do
people care about?

00:33:33.860 --> 00:33:34.770
The laptops they use.

00:33:34.770 --> 00:33:37.730
I mean, this is now the
default that everybody has.

00:33:37.730 --> 00:33:39.470
But five years ago,

00:33:39.470 --> 00:33:42.890
it was a benefit to give
people high-quality machines

00:33:42.890 --> 00:33:44.620
as opposed to optimizing our
costs and

00:33:44.620 --> 00:33:47.580
having Dell machines and ugly
monitors, just as an example.

00:33:47.580 --> 00:33:49.200
So if you think about all
these people that

00:33:49.200 --> 00:33:51.490
are relentlessly resourceful,
incredibly talented in

00:33:51.490 --> 00:33:54.150
a massively competitive
ecosystem competing for

00:33:54.150 --> 00:33:55.900
talent, you want to give the
people the best

00:33:55.900 --> 00:33:58.230
possible tools to do the best
possible job.

00:33:58.230 --> 00:34:00.950
And so, right rigorously
thinking through how do I

00:34:00.950 --> 00:34:02.510
make people more successful?

00:34:02.510 --> 00:34:03.970
What things do they not need
to be

00:34:03.970 --> 00:34:06.010
working on that are
distracting?

00:34:06.010 --> 00:34:06.910
And what things can I

00:34:06.910 --> 00:34:09.760
actually given them that make
them more valuable per day?

00:34:09.760 --> 00:34:11.200
And then just break that down
every day and

00:34:11.200 --> 00:34:12.230
solve that stuff yourself.

00:34:13.450 --> 00:34:15.640
&gt;&gt; So, when you&#39;re in a
start-up environment,

00:34:15.640 --> 00:34:17.010
how you you optimize for those
things?

00:34:17.010 --> 00:34:18.640
because, you know, resources
are scarce and.

00:34:18.640 --> 00:34:20.380
&gt;&gt; It&#39;s a good, it&#39;s a good
question.

00:34:20.380 --> 00:34:21.770
I actually think that you
should start,

00:34:21.770 --> 00:34:23.840
first of all, you must have
your own office.

00:34:23.840 --> 00:34:25.990
I don&#39;t believe ever in shared
office spaces.

00:34:25.990 --> 00:34:27.420
Peter talks a little bit about
this,

00:34:27.420 --> 00:34:29.200
that every start-up, every
good start-up is a cult.

00:34:29.200 --> 00:34:30.140
It&#39;s really hard to

00:34:30.140 --> 00:34:32.350
create a cult if you&#39;re
sharing space with people.

00:34:32.350 --> 00:34:33.290
Because a cult means that you

00:34:33.290 --> 00:34:34.860
think that you&#39;re better than
everybody else in the world,

00:34:34.860 --> 00:34:35.770
that you have a special way of
doing

00:34:35.770 --> 00:34:37.680
things that&#39;s different than
everybody else in the world.

00:34:37.680 --> 00:34:39.380
And if you&#39;re sharing physical
space with people,

00:34:39.380 --> 00:34:40.930
it&#39;s very hard to inculcate
that.

00:34:40.930 --> 00:34:43.050
So, I would start there, but

00:34:43.050 --> 00:34:44.420
it is a prioritization
question.

00:34:44.420 --> 00:34:45.370
When you have, everybody is

00:34:45.370 --> 00:34:47.240
going to have scarce
resources, just a question of

00:34:47.240 --> 00:34:50.490
magnitude like how many zeros
are you paying attention to?

