You know, probably not $10.

00:34:51.873 --> 00:34:53.628
Expenditures, put $100, then
$1,000,

00:34:53.628 --> 00:34:55.980
then 10,000, then a million,
and then 10 million.

00:34:55.980 --> 00:34:57.850
Starts being a rounding error.

00:34:57.850 --> 00:34:59.980
So, what I would do is figure
out like,

00:34:59.980 --> 00:35:00.870
what&#39;s most important?

00:35:00.870 --> 00:35:02.920
And in a high quality office,
that creates a good vibe.

00:35:02.920 --> 00:35:04.500
That allows you to recruit
people,

00:35:04.500 --> 00:35:06.000
because recruits are very
savvy about this.

00:35:06.000 --> 00:35:07.420
They walk into your office,
and

00:35:07.420 --> 00:35:09.624
they can tell a lot about the
culture instantly.

00:35:09.624 --> 00:35:12.510
I sometimes, I walk into a
company office and I can tell,

00:35:12.510 --> 00:35:15.360
often, whether I&#39;m going to
invest, as soon as I walk in.

00:35:15.360 --> 00:35:17.270
Like, I can absolutely rule
things out that I

00:35:17.270 --> 00:35:19.170
just don&#39;t want to invest in
as soon as I walk in.

00:35:19.170 --> 00:35:21.070
And there&#39;s times walking into
the office is like,

00:35:21.070 --> 00:35:22.650
wow, this is very impressive.

00:35:22.650 --> 00:35:24.230
You can tell how people worked
together,

00:35:24.230 --> 00:35:26.720
how hard they&#39;re working, how
distracted they are.

00:35:26.720 --> 00:35:29.900
Roelof Botha at Sequoia made a
point to me about YouTube.

00:35:29.900 --> 00:35:31.470
So, when I invested in
YouTube,

00:35:31.470 --> 00:35:33.410
in the very, very beginning,

00:35:33.410 --> 00:35:35.490
it wasn&#39;t obviously going to
be successful.

00:35:35.490 --> 00:35:39.310
And then, Roelof led this
series A investment for

00:35:39.310 --> 00:35:40.540
Sequoia in YouTube.

