00:35:49.740 --> 00:35:51.930
&gt;&gt; And I was like, pretty good
sign.

00:35:51.930 --> 00:35:53.710
So like, if you pick up on
these little things you

00:35:53.710 --> 00:35:54.340
can predict a lot.

00:35:56.990 --> 00:35:57.570
Yeah?

00:35:57.570 --> 00:36:00.580
&gt;&gt; What do you think is the
best way to gain street cred

00:36:00.580 --> 00:36:01.640
for a new manager?

00:36:01.640 --> 00:36:05.740
&gt;&gt; Oh boy yeah so the question
is how&#39;s the best way to

00:36:05.740 --> 00:36:08.050
grain, gain street cred for a
new manager?

00:36:09.220 --> 00:36:11.760
Almost all good managers in
Silicon Valley are promoted

00:36:11.760 --> 00:36:15.000
because of their individual
performance in cultures that

00:36:15.000 --> 00:36:17.780
are meritocratic, you know,
the percentage is even higher.

00:36:17.780 --> 00:36:20.730
So we tried at PayPal to only
promote people that

00:36:20.730 --> 00:36:22.660
were basically kicking **** at
their discipline.

00:36:22.660 --> 00:36:26.650
So Peter didn&#39;t believe in
general managers.

